explanation: Uses dynamic programming with two arrays: len[i] stores the length of the longest increasing subsequence ending at i, and cnt[i] stores the count of such subsequences. For each i, it iterates over all previous indices j to update len[i] and cnt[i]. Finally, it sums counts for indices whose length equals the global maximum length.

